SIMPLE: heraldry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heraldry
<hw>Her"ald*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art
or office of a herald; the art, practice, or science of recording
genealogies, and blazoning arms or ensigns armorial; also, of marshaling
cavalcades, processions, and public ceremonies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A coat of arms or some other heraldic device or
collection of heraldic symbols.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heraldship</ent>⟦br⟧
